title: Google\Cloud\Orchestration\Airflow\Service\V1\PrivateClusterConfig
name: PrivateClusterConfig
description:
Configuration options for the private GKE cluster in a Cloud Composer environment.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.orchestration.airflow.service.v1.PrivateClusterConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.enable_private_endpoint
params.description: Optional. If true, access to the public endpoint of the GKE cluster is denied.

params.name: data.master_ipv4_cidr_block
params.description: Optional. The CIDR block from which IPv4 range for GKE master will be reserved. If left blank, the default value of '172.16.0.0/23' is used.

params.name: data.master_ipv4_reserved_range
params.description: Output only. The IP range in CIDR notation to use for the hosted master network. This range is used for assigning internal IP addresses to the GKE cluster master or set of masters and to the internal load balancer virtual IP. This range must not overlap with any other ranges in use within the cluster's network.
